n weapon)<br><br>Solo, group, duo with Shaman ... fight in dungeons (LGuk) a little and open areas a lot. Piercing 198, 2HS 174, 1HS 164, 1HB 112, 2HB .... um, yeah, sure.<br><br>Question:  At 45 I understand that a DW helm is crucial to being able to solo effectively and pretty nice if you like playing with a shaman.  But, I don't need it yet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     What item or items would be best use of current pp or simply to try for obtainable No Drops?  <br><br><br>Eggolas Moria<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A> at: 3/8/02 11:13:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigerheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 8:59:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> I would stop useing that ghoulbane, and prob would buy a wurmslayer. At 25 dmg and 40 Del  , IT will far Out dmg your ghoulbane agaist Undead or not. More dmg = faster kills and less Dmg taken. Wurm about 1k on my server. Also sell that Shieldstorm, that dmg ratio is very bad on shieldstorm, even though it has AC + stats, the ratio is so bad its not worth using in any pratical situation. <br>             I sugest getting a Arbitors Combine great sword , again 1k or less on my server and it has superior stats, <br>30dmg 43del 15wis 25mana, It will do much more Dmg and you will be hitting well over 100 with that thing.<br><br>Hope this helps<br><br>Tigerheart 60 Pal bertoxxous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ureplay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>replay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 819<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 11:30:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.surewest.net/replay/replaysig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> You can try obtaining the No Drop 41 dmg 51 delay 2HS Strength of Grodan in Maiden's Eye. The zone is too tough at your level, but I've seen these things rot or people looting them even though they have no use for it because it would've rotted anyway. Good luck. <p>- Replay Promisekeeper, Crusader</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 1:03:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure about the stats on dwarven plate so I won't tell you to upgrade those slots.  I'd save up a little more and try to get a haste item.  It will help you a lot more in the long run. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaladril1961.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadril1961</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 249<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 1:36:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> These are the upgrades I'd go for now and in this order. You should be able to afford the first two with your 800-1k pp you have now.<br><br>Deepwater helm<br>Gauntlets of the Black<br>haste belt quest from stonebrunt<br>Hero Bracer or Iceforged Shackles <p><b>Galadril Adamante<BR>Officer, Order of the White Dragon<BR>Knight of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR><a href=mailto:sblue@bright.net>sblue@bright.net</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 2:08:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> Dwarven Plate is awesome, though Enchanted/Imbued might be better for you.  If your Smith is skilled enough, try getting some now that they've upped the AC on the Enchanted/Imubed to match the Enchanted.  Then you can sell the Enchanted to a Dwarven Warrior to cover your costs.<br><br>Arms: Enchanted/Imbued Dwarven Plate, Sebilite Scale Vambraces, Ry'Gorr Chain Sleeves (Heck, even just Imbued Dwarven Plate Vambraces would be better).<br><br>Waist: Since you're already in LGuk, try getting into the Frenzy camp for an FBSS.<br><br>I'd normally say get the DW Helm right away, but I know how good Dwarven Plate is. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Lastly... remember, as long as your Agl is above 75, you're in the clear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 4:39:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> With that little cash I'd say don't buy anything.  Hang on to the money and get the dw helm when you can.  If you have a group that is capable then camp the fbss.  After that the buy/sell thing in EC is too expensive to do if you're just grinding exp in groups and what not.  You and your group need to seek out mobs that drop the 1k+ loots so you can get a chip in the big game.  When your group isn't around, head to Rathe and solo hill giants for decent money on the side.  <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 7:07:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> When your group isn't around, head to Rathe and solo hill giants for decent money on the side.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Um...  No offence, but what did you have at level 40 that would let you (as a Paladin) solo Hill Giants?!?!?!<br><br>P.S. Don't be afraid to get an upgrade, just because you know that you'll be upgrading again when you hit the Planes/Kael/whatever...  Otherwise you'd end up wearing Bronze until you got your Shining Knights armour! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/12/02 5:57:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> IMO, it doesn't matter that you can't use the effect on DW helm yet. Get it anyway for the 21 AC <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/12/02 7:51:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 40 Upgrade with 800-1k pp</span><hr size=1> Enchanted Dwarven Plate Helm: AC 16, STR 4, STA 4, sv fire 4, sv magic 5, wt 5.0<br>Enchanted Dwarven Plate Collar: AC 10, STR 4, STA 6, sv vs fire 1, sv vs magic 4, wt 4.5<br>Enchanted Dwarven Plate Boots: AC 15, STR 8, STA 8, sv fire 2, sv magic 4, wt 7.5<br><br>Imbue adds 4 Wis, 3 Wis &amp; 4 Wis, respectively.<br><br>For other Dwarves looking for upgrades... (These are all Enchanted/Imbued Dwarven Plate.)<br>Mask AC 8, STA 4, WIS 2, sv fire 1, sv magic 4, wt 2.0<br>Belt AC 10, STR 4, STA 6, WIS 3, sv magic 3, sv fire 2, wt 4.5 <br>Bracer AC 11, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 2, sv fire 1, wt 4.5 <br>Cloak AC 11, STR 6, STA 6, WIS 4, sv magic 5, sv fire 3, wt 4.1 <br>Gauntlets AC 13, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 4, sv magic 4, sv fire 4, wt 5.5 <br>Pauldrun AC 12, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 3, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 5.0 <br>Vambraces AC 15, STR 5, STA 6, WIS 4, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 7.0 <br>Greaves AC 16, STR 8, STA 8, WIS 4, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 8.5 <br>Breastplate AC 28, STR 8, STA 10, WIS 4, sv fire 5, wt 11.5 <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=171.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=171.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=9><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpalad